Functional Dependencies

We define the functional dependencies (FDs) for the given relation.
The relation VisitData represents by the following attributes: \[ \begin{array}{l} \text{VisitData(VisitID, Restaurant, ServerEmpID, ServerName, StartDateHired,EndDateHired, HourlyRate, ServerBirthDate,}\\ \text{ServerTIN, VisitDate, VisitTime,MealType, PartySize, Genders, WaitTime, CustomerName, CustomerPhone,CustomerEmail,} \\ \text{LoyaltyMember, FoodBill, TipAmount, DiscountApplied, PaymentMethod, OrderedAlcohol, AlcoholBill)} \end{array} \] ### Functional Dependencies: \[ \begin{aligned} 1. & \quad VisitID \rightarrow Restaurant, ServerEmpID, VisitDate, VisitTime, MealType, PartySize, Genders, WaitTime, \\ & \quad CustomerName, CustomerPhone, CustomerEmail, LoyaltyMember, FoodBill, TipAmount, DiscountApplied, \\ & \quad PaymentMethod, OrderedAlcohol, AlcoholBill \\ 2. & \quad ServerEmpID \rightarrow ServerName, StartDateHired, EndDateHired, HourlyRate, ServerBirthDate, ServerTIN \\ 3. & \quad CustomerPhone \rightarrow CustomerName, CustomerEmail, LoyaltyMember \\ 4. & \quad CustomerEmail \rightarrow CustomerName, CustomerPhone, LoyaltyMember \\ 5. & \quad PaymentMethod \rightarrow PaymentMethodName \\ 6. & \quad MealType \rightarrow MealTypeName \\ 7. & \quad Restaurant \rightarrow RestaurantID \end{aligned} \]

Decomposition to 3NF

Using the functional dependencies and normalization rules, we decompose the original relation into multiple relations satisfying Third Normal Form (3NF):

Relations:

  1. Restaurant (RestaurantID, RestaurantName)
  2. Server (ServerEmpID, ServerName, StartDateHired, EndDateHired, HourlyRate, ServerBirthDate, ServerTIN)
  3. Customer (CustomerID, CustomerName, CustomerPhone, CustomerEmail, LoyaltyMember)
  4. PaymentMethod (PaymentMethodID, PaymentMethodName)
  5. MealType (MealTypeID, MealTypeName)
  6. Visit (VisitID, RestaurantID, ServerEmpID, CustomerID, VisitDate, VisitTime, MealTypeID, PartySize, Genders, WaitTime, FoodBill, TipAmount, DiscountApplied, PaymentMethodID, OrderedAlcohol, AlcoholBill)
